## 🔴 CRITICAL FINDINGS

### **CR-01: Rider Portal — Widespread Stored XSS (No Escaping)**  
**Severity:** 🔴 CRITICAL (CVSS 10.0)  
**Affected:** `rider/app.js:526-539`, `552-572`  
**CWE:** CWE-79 (Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation)

**Vulnerable Code:**
```javascript
// Line 526-539: Unassigned orders list
unassignedList.innerHTML += `
  <div class="order-card-premium">
    <div class="order-id-chip">#${(o.orderId || id.slice(-6)).toUpperCase()}</div>
    <h3 class="rest-name">Drop-off: ${o.address || 'Unknown'}</h3>
    <span class="text-orange">₹${o.deliveryFee || 0}</span>
    <button onclick="window.acceptOrder('${id}', '${outletId}')">ACCEPT</button>
  </div>`;

// Line 552-572: Active delivery view
dashboardActiveView.innerHTML = `
  <div class="active-delivery-mock-card">
    <h3>${cName}</h3>
    <p><i data-lucide="map-pin"></i> ${cAdd}</p>
    <button onclick="window.open('tel:${cPhone}')">CALL</button>
    <button onclick="window.triggerWhatsAppAlert('${cPhone}', '${oId}', 'PICKED_UP')">MSG</button>
  </div>`;
```

**Data Sources (all from Firebase, user-controlled):**
- `o.address` — Customer address from WhatsApp order (user-provided)
- `cName` — Customer name from WhatsApp order (user-provided)
- `cAdd` — Customer address (user-provided)
- `o.deliveryFee` — numeric but could be tampered via DB write
- `o.orderId`, `id` — system-generated; safer but not escaped
- `cPhone` — sanitized via `replace(/\D/g, '')` — OK for tel: link

**Impact:**  
Any customer placing an order via WhatsApp can inject malicious JavaScript into their name or address. When a rider views the order, the script executes in the rider's browser with full session access.  
**Attack scenario:**
1. Customer sends WhatsApp message with name: `<img src=x onerror=stealRiderSession()>`;
2. Bot stores this name in Firebase Orders;
3. Rider portal renders unsanitized → XSS fires;
4. Attacker steals rider's Firebase auth token, impersonates rider, can view orders, location, etc.

**Why it's worse than Admin:**  
- Admin at least uses `escapeHtml()` in most places (except 2 spots)
- Rider has `escapeHtml` function defined (line 72-80) but **never uses it** in any innerHTML rendering
- **Rider CSP is extremely weak** (`'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'`) making XSS trivial
- No SRI, no nonce — full inline script execution allowed

**Remediation:**  
Wrap ALL dynamic data with `escapeHtml()`:
```javascript
<h3>${escapeHtml(cName)}</h3>
<p>${escapeHtml(cAdd)}</p>
```
Same for unassigned list. Also replace `innerHTML +=` with DOM APIs (e.g., `createElement`, `textContent`) for maximum safety.

