### **H-03: Firebase Security Rules — Weak Admin Creation / Migration**  
**Severity:** HIGH  
**Files:** `database.rules.json:7-13`, `Admin/app.js:800-823`

Rule: `".write": "auth != null && (!data.exists() || root.child('admins/' + auth.uid).exists())"`

This allows any authenticated user to create an admin record if it doesn't exist OR if they're already an admin. A malicious user with Firebase Auth can create themselves as admin if no admin records exist.

**Fix:** Use Firebase Custom Claims instead of DB flag. Or restrict creation to first admin only:
```json
".write": "auth != null && (!data.exists() && root.child('admins').numChildren() === 0) || root.child('admins/' + auth.uid).exists()"
```
Better: Remove client-side admin creation entirely; use Admin SDK.

