### **H-05: Bot Writes Unsanitized User Data to Firebase**  
**Severity:** HIGH  
**File:** `bot/index.js:551-559`

Order creation:
```javascript
const finalOrder = {
  orderId, outlet: user.outlet, customerName: user.name,
  phone: user.phone, address: user.address,
  lat: user.location.lat, lng: user.location.lng,
  subtotal, deliveryFee: user.deliveryFee, total: subtotal + user.deliveryFee,
  status: "Placed", paymentMethod: method, paymentStatus: "Pending",
  createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),
  items: user.cart
};
await setData(`orders/${orderId}`, finalOrder, user.outlet);
```

`user.name`, `user.address` come directly from WhatsApp messages — no sanitization. Since admin/rider portals display these fields with XSS bugs, this is the **source injection point**.

**Remediation:** Sanitize before storing:
```javascript
const escapeHtml = (str) => ...; // use same as client
finalOrder.customerName = escapeHtml(user.name).trim();
finalOrder.address = escapeHtml(user.address).trim();
```
Or better: sanitize on read at presentation layer (but that requires fixing UI bugs). Defense-in-depth: sanitize at write.

