## 🟠 HIGH-RISK FINDINGS (8)

### **H-01: Rider CSP — Allows Inline/Eval (Facilitates XSS)**  
**File:** `rider/index.html:8-9`, `rider/login.html:7-8`  

```html
Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self' https: data: blob: 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval';
```

`'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'` allow any inline script and `eval()` to execute. Combined with CR-01 (XSS), this makes exploitation trivial.

**Fix:**
```html
Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self' https: data: blob:;
script-src 'self' https://www.gstatic.com https://unpkg.com;
style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com;
```
Remove `'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'` from `script-src`. Use nonce if absolutely necessary.

---

### **H-02: Firebase Rules — `feedbacks` Write Open to Any Auth**  
**File:** `database.rules.json:120-123`  

```json
"feedbacks": {
  ".read": "auth != null && root.child('admins/' + auth.uid).exists()",
  ".write": "auth != null"   // ❌ ANY authenticated user (including riders) can write
}
```

**Impact:** Riders can spam feedback with junk/fake data.

**Fix:**
```json
".write": "auth != null && root.child('admins/' + auth.uid).exists()"
```
Or create separate unauthenticated submission endpoint with validation (length, rate-limit).

---

### **H-03: Firebase Rules — Admin Creation Privilege Escalation**  
**File:** `database.rules.json:7-13`  

```json
".write": "auth != null && (!data.exists() || root.child('admins/' + auth.uid).exists())"
```

Allows any authenticated user to create admin record if no admins exist yet OR if they're already admin. Malicious user can self-elevate.

**Fix:** Use Firebase Custom Claims (Admin SDK) or restrict creation to first admin only:
```json
".write": "auth != null && (!data.exists() && root.child('admins').numChildren() === 0) || root.child('admins/' + auth.uid).exists()"
```

---

### **H-04: Firebase Rules — Rider Arbitrary Field Injection**  
**File:** `database.rules.json:28-52`  

Rider self-write rule protects only 5 specific fields but allows adding any other field:
```json
".write": "auth != null && (root.child('admins/' + auth.uid).exists() || (auth.uid == $uid && newData.child('email').val() == data.child('email').val() && ...))"
```
A rider could add `"isAdmin": true` or `"freeDelivery": true`. If any code reads these fields → privilege escalation.

**Fix:** Add field whitelist via `.validate`:
```json
".validate": "newData.hasChildren(['email','name','phone','aadharNo','profilePhoto','status','fcmToken','lastSeen']) &&
              !newData.hasChildren(['isAdmin','role','privileges'])"
```
Or move such flags to Firebase Custom Claims.

